Course.Title: CONST DOCU FOR DESIGNERS
Course.Description:
A studio/lecture course that expands the student's previous experience with the elements of architectural drawings and synthesizes them into a set of architectural construction documents. Students are required to research finishes, materials, and construction techniques to convey in a detailed way the intent of a previously designed project and produce the drawings required to construct their project.  Field experiences and printing required, fees may apply.  

Prerequisite(s): INTD 3140 and INTD 4111
